HEADWORD: Bludgeon
<hw>Bludg"eon</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Ir.
<ets>blocan</ets> a little block, Gael. <ets>plocan</ets> a mallet, W.
<ets>plocyn</ets>, dim. of <ets>ploc</ets> block; or perh. connected
with E. <ets>blow</ets> a stroke. Cf. <er>Block</er>, <er>Blow</er> a
stroke.]</ety> <def>A short stick, with one end loaded, or thicker and
heavier that the other, used as an offensive weapon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

